This paper involves the use of mobile robots and computer vision algorithms to measure tree diameters in forests, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses 3D mapping and image processing techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with forestry and environmental applications, which could potentially fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
